Rating: 4
I have to disagree with the non-stick. I used my cast-iron pan, with minimal oil. The trick is to have the heat high enough so that they form a crust rather quickly, then they flip easily. I loved the flavors. I did omit the bacon and used basil instead of thyme. The other thing I did was to add about 1/2 cup of white wine to the pan after the onion, before the corn and tomato. I covered it and let it steam. The wine reduced, mixed with the juice from the tomato. Ahhh. Delicious. Thank you for the inspiration.

Rating: 3
